    "name": "Dave Masucci",
    "profile": "DAVE MASUCCI aka \"Spyboy Sooch\" aka \"I, Storm\" : \r\nFlute, Sax, Vocals, Rap, Arranging, Production, Voice-Over Artist, DJ \r\n\r\nWilliam Paterson University (NJ)\r\nThe New School University (NYC) \r\n\r\nMany gifts & skills allow this journeyman to blend various styles of music with an effortless flow. Also known as dj I, STORM he's been known to implement his talents on sax, flute, vocals + percussion in his DJ sets.\r\n\r\nAs a MUSICIAN . . .\r\nHe has toured extensively throughout U.S. as well as Canada, Germany and Amsterdam. In 1994, his band (THE AUTHORITY) was featured on both the LOLLAPALOOZA + H.O.R.D.E. Tours... Dave returned to the H.O.R.D.E. stage in 1998 as a sideman.\r\n\r\nHe has recorded and/or shared the stage with the following artists : \r\nGeorge Clinton/Parliament Funkadelic, The Meters, Ohio Players, Chuck Brown/Soul Searchers, Graham Central Station, The Whispers, Tower of Power, ...\r\n\r\nLiving Colour, Phish, Dave Matthews Band, Spin Doctors, Blues Traveler, Widespread Panic, Fishbone",
